A hailstorm hit Xiaomeilin Village in Harqin Banner, north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region on the afternoon of June 10. The largest hailstones are the size of eggs, piling up nearly ankle-deep. Watch this video from Weather China, the China Meteorological Administration's online weather service, to find out more. (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)